HEADWORD: Acicula
<hw>A*cic"u*la</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Acicul⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a small needle,
dimin. of <ets>acus</ets> needle.]</ety> <fld>(Nat. Hist.)</fld>
<def>One of the needlelike or bristlelike spines or prickles of some
animals and plants; also, a needlelike crystal.</def>⟦br⟧
